## What's Next

Day 70 covers Task M-2 — ongoing control assessments. M-1 monitors for changes; M-2 assesses whether controls remain effective after those changes and over time. The ongoing control assessment program is how the authorization stays valid between formal re-authorization cycles — not by assuming controls continue to work, but by periodically verifying that they do.

